  • Package net.vivialconnect.model.log

    • Class net.vivialconnect.model.log.Log extends VivialConnectResource implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      -1982193020990089235L

      • Serialized Fields

        • logId

          String logId
          Unique identifier of the log object.

        • accountId

          int accountId
          Unique identifier of the account that owns this log.

        • accountIdItemId

          String accountIdItemId
          Account id item id

        • accountIdLogType

          String accountIdLogType
          Account id log type

        • accountIdOperatorId

          String accountIdOperatorId
          Account id operator id

        • logType

          String logType
          The log type as a string. Log-types are typically of the form ITEM_TYPE.ACTION, where ITEM_TYPE is the type of item that was affected and ACTION is what happened to it. For example: message.queued.

        • itemType

          String itemType
          The type of item that was affected. Possible values are number, message, account, and user.

        • itemId

          String itemId
          Unique id of item that was affected.

        • operatorType

          String operatorType
          The type of operator that generated this log. For instance, “user” for a change made by a logged-in user in the Vivia Connect console, “account” for a log created during an API request, or “admin” for an log created by the internal system.

        • operatorId

          int operatorId
          Unique id of operator that caused this log.

        • origin

          String origin
          The originating system or interface that generated the log. For instance, “web” for a change made by a logged-in user in the Vivial Connect console, “api” for API requests, or “system” for logs caused by an automated or internal system.

        • logData

          LogData logData
          A free-form json object storing additional data about the log item.

        • logDataJson

          String logDataJson
          Log data Json

        • logTimestamp

          String logTimestamp
          A UTC timestamp in format YYYYMMDDhhmmssssssss

        • description

          String description
          A human-readable description of the log.

    • Class net.vivialconnect.model.message.BulkMessage extends VivialConnectResource implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • fromNumber

          String fromNumber
          For inbound messages, the external phone number that sent the text message. Uses E.164 format (+country code +phone number). For US, the format will be +1xxxyyyzzzz. For outbound messages, the associated phone number in your account that sent the text message.

        • connectorId

          Integer connectorId
          The id of the Connector to use to send the message with

        • body

          String body
          Text body of the text message.

        • toNumbers

          List<E> toNumbers
          List of destination phone numbers for the text message in E.164 format: +1xxxyyyzzzz. Maximum list size is 100 numbers. Duplicates will be discarded.

        • mediaUrls

          List<E> mediaUrls
          URLs of the media you wish to send out with the message.

    • Class net.vivialconnect.model.message.Message extends VivialConnectResource implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      5181807107956389186L

      • Serialized Fields

        • id

          int id
          Unique identifier of the text message object

        • dateCreated

          Date dateCreated
          Creation date (UTC) of the text message in ISO 8601 format

        • dateModified

          Date dateModified
          Last modification date (UTC) of the text message in ISO 8601 format

        • accountId

          int accountId
          Unique identifier of the account or subaccount associated with the text message

        • masterAccountId

          int masterAccountId
          For subaccounts, the account_id of the subaccount’s parent (primary) account

        • messageType

          String messageType
          String identifying the type of inbound or outbound text message. Possible values: local_sms, tollfree_sms, or local_mms

        • direction

          MessageDirection direction
          Inbound/outbound direction of the text message, and if outbound, the nature of the text message initiation

        • toNumber

          String toNumber
          Phone number that received the text message. Uses E.164 format (+country code +phone number). For US, the format will be +1xxxyyyzzzz

        • fromNumber

          String fromNumber
          One of the following:

          For inbound messages, the external phone number that sent the text message. Uses E.164 format (+country code +phone number). For US, the format will be +1xxxyyyzzzz

          For outbound messages, the associated phone number in your account that sent the text message

        • connectorId

          int connectorId
          The id of the Connector to use to send the message with

        • sent

          Date sent
          One of the following in ISO 8601 format:

          For inbound messages, the UTC timestamp the text message was received

          For outbound messages, the UTC timestamp the text message was sent

        • numMedia

          int numMedia
          Number of media attachments for the text message

        • numSegments

          int numSegments
          Number of segments that make up the message

        • body

          String body
          Text body of the text message. Max. length: 1,600 characters

        • status

          String status
          Status of the message

        • errorCode

          String errorCode
          Error code, if any, for the message

        • errorMessage

          String errorMessage
          Error code message for error_code as it is displayed to users

        • price

          int price
          Amount billed for the message, in the currency associated with the account

        • priceCurrency

          String priceCurrency
          Currency in which price is measured in ISO 4127 format. For US, the currency will be USD

        • mediaUrls

          List<E> mediaUrls
          URLs of the media you wish to send out with the message.

        • bulkId

          String bulkId
          ID of the bulk to which this message belongs.

  • Package net.vivialconnect.model.number

    • Class net.vivialconnect.model.number.Number extends VivialConnectResource implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      -1224802858893763457L

      • Serialized Fields

        • id

          int id
          Unique identifier of the phone number object

        • dateCreated

          Date dateCreated
          Creation date (UTC) of the phone number in ISO 8601 format

        • dateModified

          Date dateModified
          Last modification date (UTC) of phone number in ISO 8601 format

        • accountId

          int accountId
          Unique identifier of the account or subaccount associated with the phone number

        • name

          String name
          Associated phone number as it is displayed to users. Default format: Friendly national format: (xxx) yyy-zzzz

        • phoneNumber

          String phoneNumber
          Associated phone number in E.164 format (+country code +phone number). For US numbers, the format will be +1xxxyyyzzzz

        • phoneNumberType

          String phoneNumberType
          Type of associated phone number. Possible values: local (non-toll-free) or tollfree

        • statusTextUrl

          String statusTextUrl
          URL to receive message status callback requests for messages sent via the API using this associated phone number

        • incomingTextUrl

          String incomingTextUrl
          URL for receiving SMS messages to the associated phone number. Max. length: 256 characters

        • incomingTextMethod

          CallbackMethod incomingTextMethod
          HTTP method used for the incoming_text_url requests. Max. length: 8 characters. Possible values: GET or POST

        • incomingTextFallbackUrl

          String incomingTextFallbackUrl
          URL for receiving SMS messages if incoming_text_url fails. Only valid if you provide a value for the incoming_text_url parameter. Max. length: 256 characters

        • incomingTextFallbackMethod

          CallbackMethod incomingTextFallbackMethod
          HTTP method used for incoming_text_fallback_url requests. Max. length: 8 characters. Possible values: GET or POST

        • voiceForwardingNumber

          String voiceForwardingNumber
          Number to which voice calls will be forwarded

        • city

          String city
          City where the available phone number is located

        • region

          String region
          Two-letter US state abbreviation where the available phone number is located

        • lata

          String lata
          Local address and transport area (LATA) where the available phone number is located

        • rateCenter

          String rateCenter
          LATA rate center where the available phone number is located. Usually the same as city

        • active

          boolean active

        • connectorId

          int connectorId

        • tags

          Map<K,V> tags
          Tags associated to this number instance
